               <lb facs="#facs_4_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>Prof. <rs type="person" key=", tillich_person_id__1928">Paul Tillich</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_4_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>Assistant - Mr. <rs type="person" key=", tillich_person_id__1051">Robert Kimball</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_4_tr_1_tl_8" n="N007"/>Office hours by appointment. Phone Secretary, Mrs. <rs type="person" key=", tillich_person_id__3776">Grace Leonard</rs>, UN. 8-7600, Ext. 769
               <lb facs="#facs_4_tr_1_tl_9" n="N008"/>The required work for this semester course will consist of:
               <lb facs="#facs_4_tr_1_tl_10" n="N009"/>1. A minimum of 2800 pages of outside reading. The starred selections are
               <lb facs="#facs_4_tr_1_tl_11" n="N010"/>required and will be covered on the final examination. The remainder (ca. 800 pp.)
               <lb facs="#facs_4_tr_1_tl_12" n="N011"/>of the reading may be selected at the discretion of the student.
               <lb facs="#facs_4_tr_1_tl_13" n="N012"/>2. A final examination. At the time of the examination the student should submit
               <lb facs="#facs_4_tr_1_tl_14" n="N013"/>an annotated bibliography of the reading done during the semester.
